# Preheader Requirement

Add a hidden preheader immediately after the opening `<body>` tag.

The preheader must be dynamic and based on the sermon title and/or scripture passage.

Example:

```html
<div style="display:none; max-height:0; overflow:hidden; opacity:0; color:transparent; line-height:1px; font-size:1px; mso-hide:all;">
  Watch this week's message from Blackhawk Ministries: SERMON_TITLE.
</div>
```

Also include hidden preview-text spacing after the preheader so random body content is less likely to appear in inbox previews:

```html
<div style="display:none; max-height:0; overflow:hidden; opacity:0; color:transparent; line-height:1px; font-size:1px; mso-hide:all;">
  &nbsp;&zwnj;&nbsp;&zwnj;&nbsp;&zwnj;&nbsp;&zwnj;&nbsp;&zwnj;&nbsp;&zwnj;&nbsp;&zwnj;&nbsp;&zwnj;&nbsp;&zwnj;&nbsp;&zwnj;
</div>
```

