# STEP 1: Parse Consolidated Sermon & Social JSON

You will receive a single structured JSON payload containing all sermon and social media data. Parse and extract the fields as defined below.

## JSON Schema Reference
```json
{
  "fetched_at": "2026-06-15T01:44:20.585112+00:00",
  "sources": {
    "facebook": {
      "found": true,
      "url": "https://www.facebook.com/reel/1326133276323085/"
    },
    "instagram": {
      "found": true,
      "url": "https://www.instagram.com/reel/DZVcoMfDrbI/"
    },
    "youtube": {
      "found": true,
      "url": "https://www.youtube.com/shorts/gvfPvgfRtz4",
      "thumbnail": "https://img.youtube.com/vi/gvfPvgfRtz4/maxresdefault.jpg"
    },
    "sermon": {
      "found": true,
      "data": {
        "title": "I Samuel 18:1-5",
        "description": null,
        "url": "https://blackhawk.churchcenter.com/episodes/617524",
        "video_url": "https://vimeo.com/1199197220",
        "thumbnail": "https://i.vimeocdn.com/video/2168482567-4b0830bf941999e7eab7a68df9e7cab8ba713c08901a6e0e605a4931c4ca0e13-d_1920x1080",
        "resources": []
      }
    }
  }
}
```

## Extract and Store Sermon Fields

- `SERMON_TITLE` = `sources.sermon.data.title`
- `SERMON_DESCRIPTION` = `sources.sermon.data.description`
- `CHURCH_CENTER_LINK` = `sources.sermon.data.url`
- `VIDEO_THUMBNAIL` = `sources.sermon.data.thumbnail`
- `VIDEO_LINK` = `sources.sermon.data.url`

## Important

- `VIDEO_LINK` is always the Planning Center / Church Center sermon URL (`sources.sermon.data.url`).
- Do **not** set `VIDEO_LINK` to YouTube, Facebook, Instagram, or a short-form social video.
- If `sources.sermon.data.thumbnail` is unavailable, omit the hero thumbnail background and use a dark fallback block with the play button still linking to Church Center.

---

# STEP 1B: Parse Social Media Links

Extract social media URLs directly from the JSON payload:

- `YOUTUBE_URL` = `sources.youtube.url` (if `sources.youtube.found` is true)
- `FACEBOOK_URL` = `sources.facebook.url` (if `sources.facebook.found` is true)
- `INSTAGRAM_REEL_URL` = `sources.instagram.url` (if `sources.instagram.found` is true)

## Platform URL Rules

- If a platform's `found` property is `false` or the URL is missing, omit that platform’s button entirely.
- If all three social links are unavailable, omit the entire social button row.
- Store each valid URL as a variable for use in the final HTML:

  - `YOUTUBE_URL`
  - `FACEBOOK_URL`
  - `INSTAGRAM_REEL_URL`

---

# STEP 1C: Resolve Highlight Thumbnail

## Highlight Thumbnail Resolution

Run in this order and stop at the first successful result:

1. Prompt the user:

   > Do you have a custom thumbnail URL for the Sermon Highlight share section? Paste URL or press Enter to skip.

2. If the user provides a valid HTTPS image URL:

   - Store as `HIGHLIGHT_THUMBNAIL_URL`

3. If the user skips or provides nothing:

   - Use `sources.youtube.thumbnail` if available.
   - If `sources.youtube.thumbnail` is missing but `YOUTUBE_URL` is present, extract the YouTube video ID and construct:

```text
HIGHLIGHT_THUMBNAIL_URL = https://img.youtube.com/vi/{{YOUTUBE_VIDEO_ID}}/maxresdefault.jpg
```

4. If YouTube thumbnail options are unavailable:

   - Fall back to `VIDEO_THUMBNAIL` (`sources.sermon.data.thumbnail`)

5. Store final resolved value as:

   - `HIGHLIGHT_THUMBNAIL_URL`

## YouTube ID Extraction Rules (Fallback)

If manual extraction is needed, support these YouTube URL formats:

```text
https://youtu.be/VIDEO_ID
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=VIDEO_ID
https://youtube.com/watch?v=VIDEO_ID
https://www.youtube.com/shorts/VIDEO_ID
https://youtube.com/shorts/VIDEO_ID
```

Strip query strings after the video ID.

---

# Link Destination Rules

| Email Element | Destination |
|---|---|
| Main sermon hero thumbnail with play button | `CHURCH_CENTER_LINK` |
| “Watch this week’s full sermon” quick link | `CHURCH_CENTER_LINK` |
| Highlight thumbnail | First available: `YOUTUBE_URL` → `FACEBOOK_URL` → `INSTAGRAM_REEL_URL` → `CHURCH_CENTER_LINK` |
| YouTube share button | `YOUTUBE_URL` |
| Facebook share button | `FACEBOOK_URL` |
| Instagram share button | `INSTAGRAM_REEL_URL` |
| Scripture links | `SCRIPTURE_BIBLE_URL` |
| Connect Card | `https://blackhawk.churchcenter.com/people/forms/1939` |
| Give Online | `https://blackhawk.churchcenter.com/giving` |

---

# STEP 2: Parse Key Points + Scripture Passage from Description

## Key Points

1. Split `SERMON_DESCRIPTION` by newline.
2. Find lines matching:

```regex
^\d+\.\s+(.+)$
```

3. Extract all matching key points.
4. Do **not** assume a fixed count.
5. Strip extra whitespace.
6. Remove these key point lines from the summary/theme text if the full description is also displayed as prose.
7. Store extracted key points as:

```text
KEY_POINTS[]
```

## Summary Text

Create a clean summary variable:

```text
SUMMARY_TEXT
```

Rules:

- Start from `SERMON_DESCRIPTION`.
- Remove extracted numbered key point lines.
- Remove duplicate scripture reference lines if they are standalone.
- Trim extra blank lines.
- Preserve meaningful paragraph breaks when possible.
- Escape for HTML.
- If the description is empty after removing key points, omit the summary paragraph.

---

# Scripture Passage Extraction

Extract the scripture passage reference from the description or title.

Store as:

- `SCRIPTURE_PASSAGE` — display text, for example `1 Samuel 16:1-13`

Support common passage formats:

```text
Genesis 1:1
Psalm 23
1 Samuel 16:1-13
2 Timothy 3:16-17
John 3:16
Romans 8
```

If no scripture passage can be confidently detected:

- Omit the scripture link.
- Omit scripture quick link.
- Do not output placeholder scripture text.

---

# YouVersion Bible.com Link Formatting

Bible.com links must use the **direct YouVersion Bible URL format**, not search links.

## Correct Format

```text
https://www.bible.com/bible/{{VERSION_ID}}/{{USFM_BOOK}}.{{CHAPTER}}.{{VERSE}}.{{VERSION_ABBREVIATION}}
```

## Example

For `1 Samuel 17:14` in ESV:

```text
https://www.bible.com/bible/59/1SA.17.14.ESV
```

## Required Variables

Store:

- `SCRIPTURE_PASSAGE` — display text, for example `1 Samuel 17:14`
- `SCRIPTURE_BIBLE_URL` — direct Bible.com URL, for example `https://www.bible.com/bible/59/1SA.17.14.ESV`

## Default Bible Version

Use ESV unless otherwise specified:

- `VERSION_ID` = `59`
- `VERSION_ABBREVIATION` = `ESV`

---

