# Scripture URL Construction Rules

## If Passage Includes a Single Verse

Example:

```text
1 Samuel 17:14
```

Build:

```text
https://www.bible.com/bible/59/1SA.17.14.ESV
```

## If Passage Includes a Verse Range

Example:

```text
1 Samuel 16:1-13
```

Use the **first verse of the passage** for the Bible.com URL:

```text
https://www.bible.com/bible/59/1SA.16.1.ESV
```

The display text remains:

```text
1 Samuel 16:1-13
```

## If Passage Includes a Full Chapter

Example:

```text
Psalm 23
```

Use verse `1`:

```text
https://www.bible.com/bible/59/PSA.23.1.ESV
```

The display text remains:

```text
Psalm 23
```

## Do Not Use Search Links

Do **not** use:

```text
https://www.bible.com/search/bible?q=...
```

Use direct Bible.com passage URLs only.

---

# STEP 3: Extract Resources from Response

1. Loop through the `sources.sermon.data.resources` array.
2. For each item, extract:

   - `title`
   - `url`
   - `position`

3. Filter out any resource whose URL contains:

   - `bible.com`
   - `churchcenter.com/people/forms`

4. Resource URL handling:

   - If URL is a direct image file, render as an image block.
   - Direct image file extensions:

     - `.png`
     - `.jpg`
     - `.jpeg`
     - `.gif`
     - `.webp`

   - Treat image extensions case-insensitively.
   - Ignore query strings when detecting file extension.
   - If a non-image URL passes all other filters, render it as a styled text link, **not** an `<img>` tag.

5. Sort resources by `position` ascending.
6. Use however many valid resources remain.
7. Do **not** assume a fixed count.
8. If zero qualifying resources remain, omit the entire Resources section.

---

# STEP 4: Build Email-Ready HTML

Use the visual template below, but all dynamic values must be replaced with real escaped data before final output.

---

# Play Button Rules — Critical

- The play button must be visually centered over the thumbnail.
- Use a **single-cell table**:

  - `width="100%"`
  - `height="338"`
  - `valign="middle"`

- Do **not** use a 3-row spacer approach.
- The outer `<td>` and `<a>` wrapper must have:

```css
line-height:0;
font-size:0;
```

- Add Outlook VML fallback using `<v:rect>` wrapping the inner table.
- Outlook ignores CSS `background-image` on `<td>` without VML fallback.
- Play button `<img>` uses:

```css
display:inline-block;
vertical-align:middle;
```

- Do **not** use `display:block` on the play button image.
- The thumbnail is set as a CSS `background-image` on the outer `<td>`.
- Outer thumbnail `<td>` uses:

```css
height:338px;
background-size:cover;
background-position:center center;
```

- The entire hero thumbnail clickable area points to `VIDEO_LINK`.
- `VIDEO_LINK` must equal `CHURCH_CENTER_LINK`.
- Play button uses this inline SVG data URI:

```text
data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg' viewBox='0 0 24 24' width='28' height='28'%3E%3Cpolygon points='7,3 21,12 7,21' fill='%23ffffff'/%3E%3C/svg%3E
```

- Play button circle:

```css
width:72px;
height:72px;
border-radius:36px;
background-color:rgba(0,0,0,0.65);
```

---

# Resource Section Rules

- Only render image blocks for resources that actually exist and have image URLs.
- Never render a `bible.com` URL as an `<img>` tag.
- Never render a Connect Card URL as an `<img>` tag.
- Pair image resources into rows of 2 using a `<table>`.
- If total image count is odd, the last image resource renders centered in its own row at 50% width.
- If non-image resources exist, render them below image rows as styled text links.
- If zero qualifying resources exist, omit the entire Resources section, including the heading.
- Non-image URLs that pass filtering render as styled text links inside the resources cell.
- Resource images must include meaningful `alt` text from the resource title.
- Resource image links should open the image URL in a new tab.
- Use absolute HTTPS URLs only.

---

# Connect + Giving Button Rules

- Always present.
- Never omit.
- Render as a `<table>` with two `<td>` columns.
- Do **not** use `display:inline-block`.
- Left column:

  - Connect Card button
  - `action-btn-primary`
  - teal background

- Right column:

  - Give Online button
  - `action-btn-secondary`
  - dark background

- Each button `<a>` tag has:

```css
display:block;
```

- Each button fills its column fully.
- On mobile, each button stacks to full width.

---

# Sermon Highlight Section Rules

The highlight section is built around a **clickable thumbnail image**, not a play-button hero, followed by social share buttons.

---

## Highlight Thumbnail Block

- Render `HIGHLIGHT_THUMBNAIL_URL` as a standard `<img>` tag.
- Full width:

```html
width="600"
```

- Use:

```css
border-radius:0;
```

- No play button overlay.
- Wrap the `<img>` in an `<a>` tag pointing to the first available link in this order:

  1. `YOUTUBE_URL`
  2. `FACEBOOK_URL`
  3. `INSTAGRAM_REEL_URL`
  4. `CHURCH_CENTER_LINK`

- Store that selected link as:

```text
HIGHLIGHT_LINK
```

- If no thumbnail URL can be resolved, omit the thumbnail block entirely.
- The thumbnail sits above the section label and heading inside `.highlight-cell`.

---

## Social Share Buttons

- Render below the highlight heading.
- Use a `<table>` with one `<td>` per available platform.
- Do **not** use `display:inline-block`.
- Only render buttons for platforms where a URL was successfully fetched.
- Button order, left to right:

  1. YouTube
  2. Facebook
  3. Instagram

---

## Social Button Labels

| Platform | Background Color | Label | Emoji |
|---|---:|---|---|
| YouTube | `#FF0000` | `Share on YouTube` | `▶️` |
| Facebook | `#1877F2` | `Share on Facebook` | `📘` |
| Instagram | `#E1306C` | `Share on Instagram` | `📸` |

Important: Instagram button must say:

```text
📸 Share on Instagram
```

Do **not** use:

```text
📸 Share the Reel
```

---

## Social Button Styling

Use:

```css
font-size:14px;
font-weight:700;
color:#ffffff;
border-radius:4px;
padding:14px 20px;
```

Each social button `<a>` must use:

```css
display:block;
text-align:center;
text-decoration:none;
```

---

## Social Button Layout Rules

- If 1 button:

  - Center it
  - Width: `60%`

- If 2 buttons:

  - Each button column: `49%`
  - Spacer: `2%`

- If 3 buttons:

  - Each button column: `32%`
  - Spacers: `2%`

- On mobile:

  - Each button stacks full width
  - Each button has `margin-bottom:10px`

- Add:

```html
class="social-col"
```

to each social button `<td>`.

- Add:

```html
class="social-spacer"
```

to gap columns.

---

## Highlight Section Restrictions

- No “Watch on Church Center” button inside the highlight section.
- Church Center link lives only in Quick Links.
- Social buttons must use “Share” language, not “Watch” language.
- If all three social platform URLs are unavailable, omit the entire social button row.
- If there is no thumbnail and no social row, omit the entire Highlight section.

---

# Heading Size Rules

Use these exact visual sizes:

- `Blackhawk Ministries` header:

```css
font-size:32px;
```

- Sermon title `.summary-passage`:

```css
font-size:28px;
```

- Section labels `.section-label`:

```css
font-size:13px;
letter-spacing:3px;
```

- Key points header:

```css
font-size:13px;
```

- Highlight heading:

```css
font-size:24px;
```

---

# Key Points Rules

- Render one `.key-point-row` per extracted key point.
- If zero key points are found:

  - Omit the Key Points block.
  - Omit the `<hr>` divider above it.

- Never output placeholder text like:

```text
{{KEY_POINT_1}}
```

---

