<table role="presentation" width="100%" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" border="0" style="margin-top:4px;">
  <tr>
    <td class="social-col" width="32%" valign="top">
      <a href="YOUTUBE_URL" target="_blank" class="social-btn social-btn-youtube" style="display:block; font-size:14px; font-weight:700; letter-spacing:0.5px; padding:14px 20px; border-radius:4px; text-decoration:none !important; text-align:center; color:#ffffff !important; background-color:#FF0000;">
        ▶️ Share on YouTube
      </a>
    </td>
    <td class="social-spacer" width="2%" style="font-size:0; line-height:0;">&nbsp;</td>
    <td class="social-col" width="32%" valign="top">
      <a href="FACEBOOK_URL" target="_blank" class="social-btn social-btn-facebook" style="display:block; font-size:14px; font-weight:700; letter-spacing:0.5px; padding:14px 20px; border-radius:4px; text-decoration:none !important; text-align:center; color:#ffffff !important; background-color:#1877F2;">
        📘 Share on Facebook
      </a>
    </td>
    <td class="social-spacer" width="2%" style="font-size:0; line-height:0;">&nbsp;</td>
    <td class="social-col" width="32%" valign="top">
      <a href="INSTAGRAM_REEL_URL" target="_blank" class="social-btn social-btn-instagram" style="display:block; font-size:14px; font-weight:700; letter-spacing:0.5px; padding:14px 20px; border-radius:4px; text-decoration:none !important; text-align:center; color:#ffffff !important; background-color:#E1306C;">
        📸 Share on Instagram
      </a>
    </td>
  </tr>
</table>
```

If no platform URLs exist, render nothing.

---

# Final Output Rules

Return the complete HTML only.

Before outputting final HTML, verify:

- No unresolved placeholders remain.
- No `{{` or `}}` remain anywhere in the output.
- No temporary all-caps placeholder tokens remain.
- No non-Outlook HTML comments remain.
- All dynamic text is HTML-escaped.
- All URLs are absolute HTTPS URLs.
- `VIDEO_THUMBNAIL` is set as `background-image` on `.hero-thumb-cell` inline style.
- Main sermon hero link points to `CHURCH_CENTER_LINK`.
- Main sermon hero link does **not** point to YouTube, Facebook, Instagram, or a YouTube Short.
- `VIDEO_LINK`, if used internally, equals `CHURCH_CENTER_LINK`.
- Play button uses single-cell `valign="middle"` table with VML fallback.
- No 3-row spacer is used for the play button.
- Play button `<img>` uses `display:inline-block; vertical-align:middle`.
- No `bible.com` URL appears as an `<img src>`.
- No Connect Card URL appears as an `<img src>`.
- Resources section is omitted entirely if no qualifying resources exist.
- Resource images are paired into 2-column table rows.
- If image resource count is odd, the final image renders centered at 50% width.
- Non-image resources render as styled text links.
- Connect + Giving buttons use `<table>` columns and both are visible side by side on desktop.
- Connect + Giving buttons stack full-width on mobile.
- Key points render only if found.
- Key point divider is omitted if no key points exist.
- Scripture passage links use direct YouVersion URL format, for example:

```text
https://www.bible.com/bible/59/1SA.17.14.ESV
```

- No `https://www.bible.com/search/bible?q=` links are used.
- Church Center link is present in Quick Links.
- All heading sizes match spec:

  - Header: `32px`
  - Sermon title: `28px`
  - Highlight heading: `24px`

- `HIGHLIGHT_THUMBNAIL_URL` is resolved via:

  1. Custom input
  2. YouTube `maxresdefault`
  3. Planning Center art

- Highlight thumbnail is rendered as an `<img>` tag, not a background image.
- Highlight thumbnail links to first available:

  1. YouTube
  2. Facebook
  3. Instagram
  4. Church Center

- No “Watch on Church Center” button appears inside highlight section.
- Social buttons use “Share” language, not “Watch” language.
- Instagram button says exactly:

```text
📸 Share on Instagram
```

- Social share buttons render only for platforms where a URL was successfully fetched.
- Social row is omitted entirely if all three platform URLs are unavailable.
- Social button column widths match actual button count:

  - 1 button: `60%` centered
  - 2 buttons: `49%` / `2%` / `49%`
  - 3 buttons: `32%` / `2%` / `32%` / `2%` / `32%`

- Social buttons stack full-width on mobile via `.social-col` responsive rule.
- Footer includes:

  - Blackhawk Ministries
  - Physical mailing address
  - Website link

- If the sending platform requires unsubscribe or preferences links, include the platform-provided merge tag in the footer. Do not invent an unsubscribe URL.

---

# If Data Is Missing

Use these fallback behaviors:

| Missing Data | Behavior |
|---|---|
| `SERMON_TITLE` | Use `This Week's Message` |
| `SERMON_DESCRIPTION` | Omit summary text and key points |
| `CHURCH_CENTER_LINK` | Stop and ask for the Church Center sermon URL before generating final HTML |
| `VIDEO_THUMBNAIL` | Use dark fallback hero block without background image |
| `SCRIPTURE_PASSAGE` | Omit scripture link and scripture quick link |
| `SCRIPTURE_BIBLE_URL` | Omit scripture link and scripture quick link |
| Resource list | Omit Resources section |
| Social URLs | Omit unavailable platform buttons |
| All social URLs | Omit social button row |
| Highlight thumbnail | Omit highlight thumbnail block |
| No highlight thumbnail and no social URLs | Omit entire Highlight section |

